article.headline: Shoush, Welch lead Sooners
article.linkText: Oklahoma dominates Zips in Junkanoo opener
article.story:
FREEPORT, Bahamas (AP) -- Lauren Shoush and Chelsi Welch each
scored 13 points to lead Oklahoma (No. 23 ESPN/USA Today; No. 21 AP) to an 88-40 win over Akron
in the first round of the Junkanoo Jam on Friday.

Shoush shot 4 of 7 from the field, including two 3-pointers, and
Chelsi was 3 of 7 from 3-point range for the Sooners (4-0). Leah
Rush added 11 points for Oklahoma and Laura Andrews had 10.

Courtney Stewart had nine points in a reserve role to lead the
Zips, who shot just 4 of 24 in the second half.

The Sooners dominated from the opening tipoff, grabbing 11
offensive rebounds while shooting 43 percent from the field for a
46-23 lead at halftime.

Antoinette Wadsworth grabbed 12 rebounds for Oklahoma, which
outrebounded Akron 47-27, and will take on Iowa in the championship
game Saturday. Akron faces Florida in the third-place game.
